This map is a cross between a regular barricade-building zombie map and a zombie escape map. Only you are not only running away from the zombies, but you are running away from the ceiling.

This is a reverse-zombie map. Instead of the typical "try to get to the highest point away from the zombie" gameplay style; in this map, you do the exact opposite, you try to get to the lowest point to avoid getting crushed.

Depending on how long the round time is set on your server will determine on how many times the ceiling will come down to pummel the players. In a general 5 minute round time, the ceiling will come down twice.

Features:
slowly descending ceiling for your pending doom.
a breakable raise-able wall activated by a button.
several human-sided areas that are only temporary because of the collapsing ceiling
a breakable box wall that surrounds the CT spawn.
several other unique rooms to challenge both zombie and human.

zm_courtyard is the latest zombiemod map for CS:S made by Mario™ and me. 

It features an old building with its courtyard, hence the name. Although it is an small map, and is therefore intended for an small amount of players, it has 64 spawnpoints, 32 for each team.

Its main features are:

- Small sized map, perfect for quick zombie matches.
- Climbing spots(box and ladder-based)
- 5 rooms intended for barricade
- 2 bathrooms originally planned as barricade spots but turned into hiding spots
- Detailed and realistic recreation of an old building.
- 3d skybox resembling a medium-sized city by a lake
- The radio in one of the rooms plays Metallica - For Whom The Bell Tolls

Note:
This map is created for Gun Reloading Zombie Mod and also CSS Deathmatch.  This is not a barricade type of zombie map, it is made to be realistic with high detail.  My goal was to create a realistic zombie lake map since all the other I've seen are poorly made.

Details:
The map is centered around a large lake in the middle with houses on either side.  There is also a sewer system that connects the two houses with plenty of quick exits.  The map has great creepy characteristics great for zombie invasions.

Final:
I do plan on creating more versions of this map to include better optimization, soundscapes, and different game type compatibilities.  Also I am working on creating a Hondo inspired version, if you know what I mean.

This is my first published map and I would greatly appreciate input.
My email is: rapidcore85@gmail.com
My Steam Name is: enano_salvaje

Thank you for downloading my map!

enano_salvaje

**Note**: This map is created for Zombie Mod and also CSS Deathmatch. This is not a barricade type of zombie map, it is made to be realistic with high detail. My goal was to create a realistic zombie lake map since all the other I've seen are poorly made.

**Details**: The map is centered around a large lake in the middle with houses on either side. There is also a sewer system that connects the two houses with plenty of quick exits. The map has great creepy characteristics great for zombie invasions.

**Secret**: There is a Hondo (old TFC/AHL mapper) inspired secret within the game-play.  Read the map description to figure out the clues to begin the secret.
*Note* When in the secret, don't hesitate to use the "use" button to progress though it.

**The Story to the Secret**

Only days ago, Mr Russell (owner of the white house) went missing after the the murder of his wife. Reports state from his neighbor, Mr Durant, that he was last seen on the dock bringing in his boat. The report also indicates that only 20 minutes later, Mr Durant reported hearing someone at his front door. Thinking it was Mr Russell, Mr Durant went to answer, but no one was there.

Everything about Mr Russell's disappearance and the murder of his wife correlates with the trail of a serial killer who investigators have been in pursuit of for 25 years. This serial killer has always left his murder weapon near the scene, but never left any clue to his exit. Investigators still have yet to locate the weapon at the lake, but are sure it is there somewhere.

In order to find the killer, you must find his weapons. They will lead you on the path through his memories of murders, and ultimately to him.

**Preview Video here**: [zm_countrylake](http://youtu.be/y36OEkzVE2c "zm_countrylake preview")

Please give me input! This is my only final released map, and always love suggestions to improve upon future maps.

Email: rapidcore85@gmail.com

Steam ID: enano_salvaje

Thank you for downloading my map!

Zm_Concrete_Final: By Makkon & Nubblecakes  



The finished and polished version of Zm_Concrete. The final features two new areas and a lot more camping/barricading spots. It also features improved optimization so that you won't lag-ass like in the last one. I added improved hinting for VVIS and added areaportalwindows to tunnel entries and doorways to improve blocking unnecessary rendering to improve the overall frame-rate. I got a solid 40-60 FPS in-game, which I ALWAYS get in CSS. I have CSS maxed out (including aa and af) at a resolution of 1024x768 (Due to only 256mb of video RAM) and full HDR. 

My computer has a Geforce 7900GS gpu, 3gb of RAM and a Core2Duo E6400 2.13ghz cpu. It's a Dell XPS 410...a Dell unfortunately...

Most of the time the FPS stayed between 55 and 60, and dropped down to around 43 in a few areas for, most likely, the HDR. If you hate HDR so much, DISABLE IT IN YOUR FUCKING VIDEO OPTIONS AND STOP COMPLAINING! And remember, the FPS WILL most likely drop a bit more when there's 12 humans in one camping spot because they fail so much they can't defend themselves and need 1089127312 other people behind them to survive, and especially when they're all constantly firing their mile-long clips and ejecting 100s of shells on the ground. You can't expect me to avoid this from happening...

Makkon, the original author of this map, is given full credit in his original work. I take credit only in porting his map to Zombie Mod and updating the lighting.



The map is small-med and I'd recommend no more than 24 people (that's max anyway). The map is the same exact layout as fk_stalker_concrete, but this one is daytime.


Originally I only intended this to be a private release at my friend's ZM server but I think other servers may find it useful. The map features camping and a little bit of barricading. Some of the good areas are only accessible by doing  difficult things. 

For instance:  The metal scaffolding tower at the back left corner of CT spawn has a little suspended metal grate in it that you can get into only if you shoot an oildrum below it, have someone crouch on top of it and boost you up to it. This is a rare occasion because people usually don't cooperate and it's hard to get the oil drum in the right spot and angle. By the time you have it set up to where you can access it, someone is already a zombie, and are probably right next to you. :)

There is one secret in the map that I will not give away. All I shall say is that it only works between the first and second minute of each round. After that it becomes constantly working until the round ends. This secret spot is virtually impossible to be penetrated by zombies (unless they get to the secret area before the access to it is closed, or until the zombies wait until the 3rd minute of the round); or on a rare occasion, they are blown towards it by a grenade. Even if the zombies do get to this area, it will still be kind of hard for them to get any players. But again, it usually takes like 10-30 seconds before the first zombie spawns, and you have a rare chance of getting to this said secret area anyway.


The map is in Final Beta, so I am releasing it as beta before the Final Final version (Confused?). :D


I hope that you all enjoy this. And please spare the time to assess if you post or even view and are a registered user here at FPSB. I don't care if your assessment isn't a 10, or a 9, or an 8, or even a 7; AS LONG AS YOU SUPPORT IT AND JUSTIFY WHY YOU GAVE ME THE ASSESSMENT! 

Please don't just say "This map is gay" and give it a 1/10 or something. 

And remember, most of the credit goes to Makkon for his original work.


*Coming Soon in Final*

-Improved Volumetric Lighting (more accurate)

-Full HDR Lighting
 
-More spots

-Brightening of certain dark areas.

-Improved shadows. A lot of areas are a bit high in lightmap scales. I'll probably just go ape shit and make all the faces have a lightmap scale of 2.


Merry Christmas!

This map shares many style similarities with my first zombie map, zm_cabin, but has many differences. Rooms are larger and not as compact//confusing as those in cabin. Also, I learned how to make area portals with doors. Coupled with using fun_details from the very start, the area portal doors have let this map have wildly improved frame rates. On my junk computer, the average rate is around 40FPS, but I've seen up to 70 in some areas. On my dedicated server test players with better comps have reported even better rates. The map has three custom textures packed into it, they're humorous motivational posters and can be found in the security rooms next to T-Spawn. The map itself isn't particularly complicated like it's name suggests, but it's got some very abstract features, such as a barn house outdoors underneath some rooms which can't be seen because the sky is in the way. WTF? Anyway, I hope y'all enjoy this map. --UPDATED MAY 21 2007-- - New room was added - Added Cubemaps - Deleted some entities that I believe caused some problems New filename is zm_complication_v2.bsp

ZM_COMPLEX is an indoor map, taking place in a sort of industrial facility. In this complex, the scientists were experimenting with a rare form of virus-DNA which brought the dead to life. When attempting to transfer the virus to its holding room one day, the virus escaped it's container, and all hell broke loose. The building was cleaned and labeled as condemned.

Now, a year later, the Terrorist faction plan on overtaking the complex and taking anything that was left of the virus back to a holding cell so that they may discover its secrets and unleash the deadly formula in a dirty bomb. The Counter-Terrorist Unit got a tip the Terrorists were planning to overtake the building, and have orders to remove any harmful substances and Terrorists from the complex.

Little do they know, the deadly virus is replicating in each room. Anyone could become infected at anytime now that its prey has entered the facility. What will you do when you're forced against a corner, the only one left, firing at a bloodthirsty, undead Terrorist? Well, there's only one way to find out, now isn't there?


PLEASE NOTE:
Screenshots do not display decals and tags. If you're wondering why there's nothing on the walls, it's because I'm using a performance configuration file to save FPS. Screenshots will be updated soon, but make sure you're not assessing a map that you haven't played.

**INFO** This is a fairly large map, spesifically designed for Zombie HUNTING, but should work just as well for regular Zombie Mod. **BULK CONSTRUCTION** It is mainly comprised of corridors and hallways. I've tried to keep the amount of campable safe-havens to a minimum, but there are still defendable positions, though they are few and far between. There are several sizable rooms in the map, so expect sh*t to go down here. The map is riddled with crates and obstacles, and there are plenty of places to hide, adding to the suspense and atmosphere. There are 4 floors, 3 different spawns including both T's and CT's, 2 elevators and plenty of staircases. The map is built to be flexible and adaptable to most situations since the map is very interconnected. The map features both well lit areas as well as areas where the flashlight is mandatory for proper navigation. The map is balanced to the best of my ability. It contains few/none secrets, in order not to make the game unbalanced for either humans or zombies. I hope you and your zombie friends will have much fun with this. [Here](http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=y5H0cGnnhRw "Here") is a video I made, showcasing the map briefly. Enjoy! ====== ### This map is dedicated to the Elite-Hunterz Zombie servers.
